HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 156
BY REPRESENTATIVES WALTERS, JACKSON, AND PHELPS
CONDOLENCES: Expresses the condolences of the House of Representatives on the death
of Kirby Shawn Dawson
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To express the condolences of the House of Representatives upon the death of Kirby Shawn
3 Dawson.
4 WHEREAS, it is with immense sadness and profound regret that the House of
5 Representatives of the Legislature of Louisiana has learned of the passing of Kirby Shawn
6 Dawson; and
7 WHEREAS, Kirby Shawn Dawson was born on May 28, 1971, to Otis and Sara
8 Dawson and was a lifelong resident of Caddo Parish; he graduated from Huntington High
9 School in 1989, attended Southern University, and earned a bachelor's degree in criminal
10 justice from Wiley College; and
11 WHEREAS, Mr. Dawson began his law enforcement career in 2002 and served with
12 the Caddo Parish Sheriff's Office before joining the Shreveport City Marshal's Office in
13 2005; he served in numerous roles throughout his career, including court deputy, outside
14 deputy, court supervisor, and assistant chief deputy; and
15 WHEREAS, Mr. Dawson was passionate about his work with the D.A.R.E. Program,
16 with which he held leadership roles across Louisiana; he possessed a special gift for
17 connecting with young people and always took time to encourage, uplift, and speak to them;
18 and
19 WHEREAS, Mr. Dawson cared deeply about his community and found purpose in
20 serving the people around him; he was respected for his leadership and dedication and
21 beloved for the genuine care and concern he had for others; and
